ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

Trial of study
Session of trial
Notes: 0 = Baseline; 1 = Session one; 2 = Session two; 3 = One-month follow-up

ElementDescription: Site
Treatment group
I am ready to make changes to enhance satisfaction in sexual relationships.
It is important to me to make changes to enhance satisfaction in sexual relationships.

How confident are you that you could make this change if you wanted to?
Notes: 1=Not at all confident; 5=Somewhat confident; 10=Extremely confident; 99 = Not applicable or prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: How committed are you to using a light box?
Notes: 1=Not at all committed; 5=Somewhat committed; 10=Extremely committed; 99 = Not applicable or prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: How important is using a light box compared to other things you have to accomplish this week?
Notes: 1=Not at all important; 5=Somewhat important; 10=Extremely important; 99 = Not applicable or prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: How much do you believe that making this change will help you achieve your personal health and wellness goals?
Notes: 1=Not at all useful; 5=Somewhat useful; 10=Extremely useful; 99 = Not applicable or prefer not to answer

ElementDescription: Timepoint/visit label
Notes: e.g., Baseline, 6-Month Follow Up, Year 2; Morning, At Bedtime
